        "title": "Tips",
        "subtitle": "Lessons learned from other facilitators.",
        "bodyHtml": "<ul>\n<li>Create a “safety valve”—designate a quiet space or support person where anyone can go if the process becomes too intense</li>\n<li>Set the tone carefully: this requires psychological safety and genuine permission to be vulnerable</li>\n<li>Make participation truly optional—never pressure anyone to be a grief walker</li>\n<li>Remind witnesses that their role is to be present, not to fix or advise</li>\n<li>The hand on the shoulder should be gentle and respectful—check in about physical touch preferences first</li>\n<li>Allow silence—don’t rush between stations or fill pauses with commentary</li>\n<li>Consider doing this later in a workshop series when trust has been built</li>\n</ul>"
