        "subtitle": "Don't make the same mistakes.",
        "bodyHtml": "<ul>\n<li>Rushing through the structure or treating it casually—this requires time and reverence</li>\n<li>Skipping the debrief—integration is essential for making meaning of the experience</li>\n<li>Using this structure too early with a group that doesn’t yet have sufficient trust</li>\n<li>Forcing positivity or jumping to “solutions” before grief has been fully honored</li>\n<li>Having witnesses offer advice or commentary—their role is presence, not problem-solving</li>\n<li>Using this structure when you (as facilitator) aren’t prepared to hold intense emotion</li>\n</ul>"
